WHAT IS THIS FILE
The mathematical model of an optical attention mechanism inspired by human
selective visual attention. It describes how a lens system can dynamically
allocate its resolving power to regions of interest, mimicking the foveated
nature of human vision.

WHY IT EXISTS
Conventional lenses image the entire field with uniform resolution, wasting
pixels. Bio-inspired attention optics (Harbin Institute, 2025) can improve
efficiency and reduce data rates. GIOP standardizes the model for pipeline
integration.

HOW IT WORKS
1. Principle:
   The human eye has high resolution only in the fovea (central ~2°). An
   optical attention system mimics this by dynamically modulating the point
   spread function (PSF) across the field of view.

2. Implementation:
   A deformable mirror, liquid crystal spatial light modulator, or tunable
   acoustic gradient lens is placed at the aperture stop. This element
   introduces a spatially varying phase:
     φ(x,y) = α(x,y) * (x² + y²)
   where α(x,y) defines the local focal length: f_local(x,y) = f_base + Δf * A(x,y).
   A(x,y) ∈ [0,1] is the attention map derived from a saliency model.

3. Saliency model:
   A(x,y) is computed from image content (contrast, motion, faces). It is
   a Gaussian mixture centered on attended regions:
     A(x,y) = sum_i w_i exp(-((x-x_i)² + (y-y_i)²) / (2σ_i²))
   where (x_i,y_i) are attention points from eye tracking or content analysis.

4. Resulting PSF:
   The PSF is space-variant. In attended regions, the lens is well-focused
   (sharp, diffraction-limited). Outside, defocus blur increases proportionally
   to (1 - A(x,y)).
   The blur diameter b(x,y) = (Δf / f#) * (1 - A(x,y)).

5. Image reconstruction:
   The raw sensor data is blurred in a known, spatially varying manner.
   A space-variant deconvolution (Richardson-Lucy with local kernels, or a
   neural network trained on the attention map) restores uniform sharpness.

6. Metadata:
   The attention map A(x,y) and the PSF parameters (f_base, Δf, f#) are
   embedded as GIOP metadata alongside the raw frame. This ensures the
   reconstruction path is fully documented and reproducible.

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
- Robotics (efficient scene understanding)
- Surveillance (high-res on faces, low-res on background for privacy/data savings)
- Autonomous vehicles (foveated perception)
- Smartphone cameras (processing power and battery saving)

WHO USES IT
L1 Architects designing attention-based optics; L2 Engineers implementing
space-variant deconvolution in ISP pipelines.

WHAT PROBLEM IT SOLVES
Enables cameras to emulate human foveation without mechanical parts,
dramatically reducing sensor readout and processing load while maintaining
perceptual quality. GIOP captures the attention map as metadata, preserving
the full reconstruction path and allowing downstream VFX to understand
exactly where and how the image was sharpened.

